                <p>On his new paper for Royal Society on a point of leaf arrangement. Asks CD to communicate it and "gives some details of its contents", e.g., recorded observations of changing leaf-order on individual specimens.</p>
                <p>Comments on a paper by George Henslow ["<hi rend="italic">Helianthus tuberosus</hi>", <hi rend="italic">Trans. Linn. Soc. Lond.</hi> 26 (1876): 647].</p>
